snippet.textDisplay: On the eve of the 2019 Taiwan Falun Dafa Experience Sharing Conference, an estimated 6,000 practitioners gathered at Liberty Square in Taipei on November 16, 2019, to do the exercises and participate in a large-scale character formation.  The character formation celebrated the practice of Falun Dafa (also known as Falun Gong) and the fact that it is practiced throughout the world. Besides thousands of practitioners from Taiwan, another 1,150 Dafa practitioners from 18 countries – including Japan, Vietnam, Korea, Malaysia, Indonesia, Philippines, Argentina, Ukraine, U.S., Spain, Russia, Hong Kong, Macau, Canada, Germany, Australia, Israel, and Brazil – also took part in the activities.
